SOFIA, Sept 8 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Monday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- Three people have died in floods following torrential rains that have swelled rivers in southeastern Bulgaria. (24 Chasa, Trud, Monitor, Presa, Duma, Standart) TRUD - A new legislation aimed to boost protection of depositors at the commercial banks is preparing a council of economists, backed by the country's leading business organisations and trade unions. -- Prosecutors will shed light on the people, who were responsible of putting a "lid" over the troubled Corporate Commercial Bank <6C9.BB>, which the chief prosecutor Sotir Tsatsrov said has operated under the protection of the state. (Standart, Sega, Presa)